    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A process of relief etching, usually on zinc plates, used in the 19th century to reproduce existing printed material, including drawings and pages of type.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000025071/Harrod's Librarians' Glossary (1984)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Proceso de grabado en relieve, habitualmente en placas de zinc, utilizado en el siglo XIX para reproducir material impreso existente, incluyendo dibujos y páginas de tipos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
